noun.description: Any of various spinous saltwater or freshwater fishes, specifically a stickleback (family Gasterosteidae).

origin: Late Middle English. Apparently cognate with or formed similarly to Middle Dutch stekelinc (Dutch stekeling), Middle Low German stekelinc, stickelinc, Middle High German stichelinc (German Stichling)<br>late 16th century. From stickle + -ing.
